<section>
<section id="slide-org84a8e51">
<h2 id="org84a8e51">Justifications</h2>
<ul>
<li>Pierre de Coubertin (first IOC president, founder of modern Olympics):</li>

</ul>
<blockquote nil>
<p>
Women have but one task, that of the role of crowning the winner with garlands … in public competitions, women’s participation must be absolutely prohibited. It is indecent that spectators should be exposed to the risk of seeing the body of a women being smashed before their eyes.
</p>
</blockquote>

<ul>
<li>Gian Franco Kasper (head of International Ski Federation): Ski jumping is not "appropriate for ladies from a medical point of view."</li>

</ul>
</section>
